<unclear/> Girl, your diary bring back so many pleasant times of your visit with us last Summer, I wish it were going to be repeated this summer again. 
We are expecting Grace sometime ^after the <unclear/> of File. They have sold and are expecting to locate here! Won't that be fine. 
Mother likes it here and I hope will be satisfied to stay with me. 
Mrs. Brown is well and so anxious to get away from Bancroft. I do hope she can come down here this spring. Met mrs. <unclear/>. She had fallen on the ice and hurt her self badly, had a supper with her. Mrs. Brown and I took Supper with her. She asked about you. as did Mrs. Bailey and mr. White. I was glad to get out of Bancroft. walked around our places but it did not make me home sick. 
Dear little girl I thank you so much for your thotfulness to me and come again next summer. 
My best love to you my dear girl and best wishes for the New Year and all the years. 
from 
Alice M. Neihardt
Branson Mo 
Jan. 14 1923. 
